uity Sticks to share. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses: "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"They wear a hard hat. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"They wear goggles. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"They lift carefully. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Interactive Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share a pen with children as you work together to describe and write about why they build things. Encourage them to use new words they learned about building this week."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What does the dog wear to stay safe?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The dog wears a hard h"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"____"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(hat) "}]},{"type":"text","text":"to stay safe. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The dog wears a hard hat to stay safe."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What are some other ways to stay safe while you are building?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Multilingual Learners "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Every vocabulary card includes an Act It Out step and a photograph to help multilingual learners—indeed, all students—to access the vocabulary. Additionally, you can model and have children act out vocabulary words when possible. These multiple approaches are particularly helpful to children with limited English proficiency."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_4","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"let’s create"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  Week 4: Build It"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_4","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About Building Materials "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lead children in a discussion about how different kinds of building materials are good for different things. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Would marshmallows or blocks work better for building a tall tower? Why?"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Explain that if one kind of building material doesn’t work, children can switch to another kind to see if it works better. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Being flexible and trying new things helps us solve problems and have fun!"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_4","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce two new words about building materials.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 6.4.4 Vocabulary Cards. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"straw sticks"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Big Chart of Big Ideas "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the Big Chart 6.4.4. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This week we are going to read "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The Three Little Rabbits."}]},{"type":"text","text":" It is a narrative about three rabbits and their houses. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Pablo Stick Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Pablo loves to read narratives about animals building things. "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect the Texts "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ready, Set, Build! and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The Three Little Rabbits"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are both stories about animals who build things. Let’s see what’s the same about these two texts! "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Concept Question "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"As we read the Big Chart, let’s think about how it connects to this week’s concept question: "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why do we build things?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Big Idea "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read aloud the teacher text on the Big Chart. Then use these prompts to read and discuss the child-facing poster together. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Equity Sticks during reading to choose children to respond. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Picture 1 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What did the first rabbit build a house with? What else can straw be used for?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"straw"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Picture 2  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What did the second rabbit use to build a house?  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"sticks"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Picture 3  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Which words rhyme? Which of the three houses do you think will be the strongest? Why? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review Make a Prediction Strategy Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Pictures 4–5 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What happened when the wolf blew on the house made of straw? What happened when the wolf blew on the house made of sticks? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Picture 6 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Which building material worked best: straw, sticks, or bricks? Why do you think that is? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How is this story and Ready, Set, Build! alike? How are they different? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Distribute three different kinds of building materials that promote fine-motor development—such as blocks, sticks or straws, and clay—to small groups. Invite children to build a house. Explain that if one kind of material or building idea doesn’t work well, they should try something new. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide a prompt about building, and guide children’s responses."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Fine Motor Skills "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Good motor skills are considered important for children’s physical, social, and psychological development. Building with materials such as blocks and clay is not only fun, but also helps to develop children’s fine-motor skills. Encourage them to experiment with different kinds of materials to help develop fine-motor movement and control."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_5","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"let’s create"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  Week 4: Build It"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Be a B